<exercise checkit-seed="0002" checkit-slug="LT4" checkit-title="Continuity">
    <statement>
        <ol>
            <li>
                <p>Determine the value of <m>b</m> to make <m>f(x)</m> continuous at <m>x=-2</m>. Explain your reasoning using limits.</p>
                <p>
                    <me>
                        f(x) = \begin{cases}
                        b x^{2} + 2 \, x + 6, &amp; x &lt; -2 \\
                        -x^{2} - 10 \, x - 17, &amp; x \geq -2
                        \end{cases}
                    </me>
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
Classify the type of discontinuity present at <m>x=4</m> for 
the function <m>g(x)</m>. Explain your reasoning using limits. </p>
                <p>
                    <me>
                        g(x) = \begin{cases}
                        -8 \, x + 30, &amp; x &lt; 4 \\
                        -3, &amp; x = 4 \\
                        -4 \, x + 14, &amp; x &gt; 4 \\
                        \end{cases}
                    </me>
                </p>
            </li>
        </ol>
    </statement>
    <answer>
        <ol>
            <li>To make <m>f(x)</m> continuous at <m>x=-2</m>, let <m>b=-\frac{3}{4}</m>.</li>
                <li>
The function <m>g(x)</m> has a
removable discontinuity.
                </li>
        </ol>
    </answer>
</exercise>
